I found a regression of the new modifier key handler (OnRawKeyEvent in MonoGame.Framework.WinFormsGameWindow) on a Dell laptop.  It was issuing events with KeyboardInputEventArgs.MakeCode 0x2a that are not related to left shift.  After some experimentation, the following stricter interpretation worked for me on my ThinkPad and the Dell:

``` C#
private void OnRawKeyEvent(object sender, KeyboardInputEventArgs args)
        {
            if (KeyState == null)
                return;

            XnaKey xnaKey;
            switch (args.Key) {
            case Keys.ShiftKey:
              xnaKey = args.MakeCode == 0x2a ? XnaKey.LeftShift : XnaKey.RightShift;
              break;
            case Keys.ControlKey:
              xnaKey = (args.ScanCodeFlags & ScanCodeFlags.E0) != 0 ? XnaKey.RightControl : XnaKey.LeftControl;
              break;
            case Keys.Menu:
              xnaKey = (args.ScanCodeFlags & ScanCodeFlags.E0) != 0 ? XnaKey.RightAlt : XnaKey.LeftAlt;
              break;
            default:
              xnaKey = (XnaKey)args.Key;
              break;
            }

            if (args.State == SharpDX.RawInput.KeyState.KeyDown && !KeyState.Contains(xnaKey))
                KeyState.Add(xnaKey);
            else if (args.State == SharpDX.RawInput.KeyState.KeyUp)
                KeyState.Remove(xnaKey);
        }
```

I have found a way to get Video playback working in Android again.
The only issue is that is circumvents the Content pipeline as the videos must reside in the Raw directory in resources.

the windows fix uses a c# wrapper for directshow (modified from this source, http://xnadsplayer.codeplex.com/)

the new approach uses a VideoView instead of the player directly.

Activity.cs (got this from http://monogame.codeplex.com/discussions/284970)

``` csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle bundle)
{
      base.OnCreate(bundle);        
      Game1.Activity = this;
      var g = new Game1();

     FrameLayout fl = new FrameLayout(this);
     fl.AddView(g.Window);
     videoView = new VideoView(this);
     videoView.Id = 2;        
     var layoutParams = new      ViewGroup.LayoutParams(ViewGroup.LayoutParams.MatchParent, ViewGroup.LayoutParams.MatchParent);
     fl.AddView(videoView, layoutParams);
     SetContentView(fl);
     MediaController mc = new MediaController(this);       
     mc.Visibility = ViewStates.Gone;
     videoView.SetMediaController(mc);
     videoView.Clickable = false;

     g.Run();
}
```

This bit of code would be in place of the current video player (this is straight from our engine and would need to be modified to fit monogame)

VideoPlayer.cs

``` csharp
public void Play(string name, bool loop = true)
        {
            Video video = (Video)m_factory.GetVideo(name);
            m_currentVideo = video.Name;

#if ANDROID
            int id = m_videoView.Context.Resources.GetIdentifier(video.Name, "raw", m_videoView.Context.PackageName);
            Android.Net.Uri movU = Android.Net.Uri.Parse("android.resource://" + m_videoView.Context.PackageName + "/raw/" + id);
            m_videoView.SetVideoURI(movU);

            m_videoView.RequestFocus();
            m_videoView.SetZOrderOnTop(true);
            m_videoView.Start();
#elif WINDOWS
            m_player.InitVideo(string.Format(@"Content\{0}\{1}.{2}",m_settings.VideoDirectory, video.Name, video.Type.GetEnumDescription()));
            m_player.Play();
#endif

            m_isPaused = false;
            m_isPlaying = true;
            m_loop = loop;
        }

        public void Stop()
        {
            m_isPlaying = false;

#if ANDROID
            m_videoView.StopPlayback();
#elif WINDOWs
            m_player.Stop();
#endif            
        }

        public void Pause()
        {
            m_isPaused = true;

#if ANDROID
            m_position = m_videoView.CurrentPosition;
            m_videoView.StopPlayback();
#elif WINDOWS
            m_player.Pause();
#endif
        }

        public void Resume()
        {
            m_isPaused = false;

#if ANDROID
            m_videoView.SeekTo(m_position);
            m_videoView.Start();
#elif WINDOWS
            m_player.Play();
#endif
        }
```

