The pre-defined colors are currently accessed as static property accessors. Any property accessor is horribly slow as compared to field access.

The following code should be replaced with a single static instance of the color:

```
    /// <summary>
    /// AntiqueWhite color (R:250,G:235,B:215,A:255).
    /// </summary>
    public static Color AntiqueWhite
    {
        get
        {
           return new Color(0xffd7ebfa);
        }
    }
```

Change to:

```
    public static Color AntiqueWhite = new Color(0xffd7ebfa);
```

Why? Because Color is a struct so no matter what path you take, you are always getting a copy of the "new", which is also painfully slow as compared to the quick stack copy from an existing instance of a struct.
